<h2 id='sub-6-2' class='sec-h2'><span>6.2 Custom Objects</span> <em class='brass'>(17)</em></h2>
<table class='tbl'>
<thead><tr>
<th><strong>API name</strong></th>
<th><strong>Sharing</strong></th>
<th><strong>Purpose</strong></th>
<th><strong># Fields</strong></th>
</tr></thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td><strong>Vehicle__c</strong></td>
<td>Private</td>
<td>Central entity representing each vehicle in the fleet. Tracks vehicle details, status, mileage, maintenance dates, and inspection information. Referenced by nearly all business requirements.</td>
<td><strong>23</strong></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Vehicle_Status_History__c</strong></td>
<td>ControlledByParent</td>
<td>Audit trail recording every change to a vehicle's Condition_Status__c. Created automatically by Flow when status changes (BR-002).</td>
<td><strong>5</strong></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Rental_Contract__c</strong></td>
<td>Private</td>
<td>Represents a rental agreement between LogiFleet and a client for a specific vehicle. Tracks contract lifecycle, billing, and expiration alerts (BR-003, BR-004, BR-010, BR-014).</td>
<td><strong>14</strong></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Maintenance_Activity__c</strong></td>
<td>Private</td>
<td>Consolidated maintenance object (per Emma's recommendation) representing both logged maintenance activities and scheduled maintenance. Covers BR-006, BR-007, BR-009, BR-019, BR-020.</td>
<td><strong>18</strong></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Sinistre__c</strong></td>
<td>Private</td>
<td>Consolidated object for insurance claims and incidents (per Emma's recommendation, merging Sinistrec and Claimc from BR-011 and BR-013). Tracks incidents, resolution, and insurance claim details.</td>
<td><strong>13</strong></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Involved_Party__c</strong></td>
<td>ControlledByParent</td>
<td>Tracks third parties involved in an incident/claim (BR-011). Child of Sinistre__c.</td>
<td><strong>4</strong></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Insurance_Policy__c</strong></td>
<td>Private</td>
<td>Consolidated insurance policy object (per Emma's recommendation, merging Insurance_Policyc and Vehicle_Insurancec from BR-012 and BR-024). Tracks policy details, coverage, and claim aggregation.</td>
<td><strong>12</strong></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Invoice__c</strong></td>
<td>Private</td>
<td>Represents monthly invoices generated for active rental contracts. Tracks billing, payment status, and overdue flagging (BR-014, BR-015).</td>
<td><strong>11</strong></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Invoice_Generation_Log__c</strong></td>
<td>Private</td>
<td>Audit log for monthly invoice generation batch runs (BR-014). Tracks success/failure of each generation cycle.</td>
<td><strong>6</strong></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Incident_Report__c</strong></td>
<td>Private</td>
<td>Mobile-submitted incident reports by drivers (BR-016). Captures real-time incident information with photo attachments.</td>
<td><strong>6</strong></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Mileage_Reading__c</strong></td>
<td>Private</td>
<td>Records individual mileage/odometer readings submitted by drivers or fleet staff (BR-017, BR-022). Supports anomaly detection and trend analysis.</td>
<td><strong>12</strong></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Driver_Vehicle_Assignment__c</strong></td>
<td>Private</td>
<td>Junction object managing the assignment of drivers (Contacts) to vehicles (BR-018). Enforces one active assignment per vehicle and per driver.</td>
<td><strong>5</strong></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Alert__c</strong></td>
<td>Private</td>
<td>Consolidated alert object (per Emma's recommendation, merging Inspection_Alertc, Insurance_Alertc, and Alertc from BR-008, BR-021, BR-024). Tracks all types of fleet alerts with Alert_Typec differentiation.</td>
<td><strong>12</strong></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Fleet_Metric__c</strong></td>
<td>Private</td>
<td>Daily snapshot of aggregated fleet metrics for dashboard display and trend analysis (BR-019).</td>
<td><strong>11</strong></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Problem_Report__c</strong></td>
<td>Private</td>
<td>Mobile-submitted problem reports by drivers for vehicle issues (BR-023). Supports assignment workflow and resolution tracking.</td>
<td><strong>12</strong></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Alert_Configuration__mdt</strong></td>
<td>N/A</td>
<td>Custom metadata type for configuring alert lead times and behavior (BR-021). Allows administrators to adjust alert thresholds without code changes.</td>
<td><strong>5</strong></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Maintenance_Alert_Setting__mdt</strong></td>
<td>N/A</td>
<td>Custom metadata type for maintenance-specific alert configuration (BR-009). Configures days before alert, notification method, and recipient.</td>
<td><strong>3</strong></td>
</tr>
